title: 【雑談】おはなししよ？【百鬼あやめ/ホロライブ】
name: Nakiri Ayame

entries.text: Things were a bit hectic just now.
My voice is a little loud, isn't it?
The reason I started streaming all of a sudden
is because I wanted to chat.
Just a little bit more, right?
I figured I should ask people to subscribe.
A "silent but I'm gonna say it" goal.
I feel like I haven't done a chatting stream since the New Year.
Even during the Ehomaki stream the other day, I didn't really get to talk slowly.
Wait, what was I trying to do just now?
I was going to put up my stream screen.
It might loop back, but just wait a sec.
But yeah, since I started streaming so suddenly,
I didn't have time to think about what to talk about.
I was thinking, "Eh, what do I do? What should I talk about?"
I've been having quite a few dance lessons.
But even though I say dance lessons,
Maybe that? I can talk a little about that.
Usually when I dance, it's mostly just learning choreography.
I thought I should properly learn the basics.
Yeah, I went to like a joint practice session.
I asked, "What kind of stuff do you do?"
"Suisei-chan, I wanna go too, what's it like?"
"And then some rhythm lessons and stuff."
So I was like, "Oh, it's fun!?"
"That sounds great! I'll go, I'll go!"
So I went, and I've been going quite a few times now, but...
We do muscle training combined with flexibility.
You guys might not know this,
Where you sit like an L-shape.
And you go "Hnnng" and reach forward.
It feels like the back of my knees are going to tear.
"And touch the floor with your hands."
Just leaning forward slightly makes me go,
the focus is on learning the moves.
Even if we stretch at the start,
So we don't spend much time on it.
I've been running away from it.
And I'd be like, "Yes, my body hurts..."
But this time, it's basic training.
So we go hard, really hard.
It's a heavy part of the menu.
Doing the splits is obvious to them.
Like there's no way I can do that!
How many degrees can I open now?
Maybe my legs open that much now.
Sitting up straight and bending forward is super hard...
For a stiff person, I can apparently open them relatively wide.
They told me, "For someone stiff, you can open up a bit."
The teacher goes around in order.
"Okay, grab my arms and I'll pull you, *squee ze*."
Usually I'm sitting on the edge.
And get pulled *gaaa* by the teacher, stretching.
I watch that with a look of despair.
"Oh god, I'm next. Oh god. Oh god."
And every time I get pulled...
I'm screaming "It hurts! It hurts! It hurts!"
The teacher laughs at me every time.
Like my organs are being crushed.
I'm screaming like I'm being mangled.
From the bottom of my stomach.
We have this exchange every time.
seeing someone stretch while making noises like that.
I've breathed out everything I have!
Thinking, "If I breathe out, maybe I can stretch more?"
After going through that flexibility hell...
The muscle training is tough too.
Above all, the tempo is fast.
I can't lift them at all.
so I can still enjoy it.
I definitely couldn't do it alone.
The teacher is super into it.
The teacher does this every day to teach.
Of course they can do it lightly.
The teacher does it every day.
Maybe not strictly every day, but...
Compared to going to a gym for muscle training,
Mentally, it's way easier to do.
I'm doing that about once a week recently.
Before, when there were concerts or events,
I'd vaguely start practicing a bit beforehand.
I'd ask the teacher for choreography.
"This time the choreo is like this~"
So I never really did detailed stuff like this before.
Crap, I used them all up recently.
I like it quite a bit.
It might be like a hobby.
I had to retake that part so many times.
Yeah, the Alesion song is up on Pekora's channel now.
Towa, Pekora, and I—the three of us sang it.
I was just talking about that.
Was it yesterday? Did it go up yesterday?
Saves me too much. The lyrics are...
I might only be singing quirky songs.
"Sore Sore Ondo" and the Alesion song.
True, mostly strong quirks so far.
Wait, I'm gonna get tissues, hang on.
Speaking of which, seriously, pollen quality recently...
I feel it intensely, how about you?
My nose is running so much.
Hey, hey, hey, isn't it early?
Like, the time when you feel pollen...
Isn't it a bit too early?
How is it, Hay Fever Masters?
I'm gonna blow my nose a bit.
Ragweed is during this cold season, right?
Then what is it now? Ragweed and...
I knew it. Is it Cedar?
Usually it gets a bit warmer...
You usually feel it when spring arrives.
Yesterday and today, isn't it freezing?
It suddenly got warm in the afternoon.
Sleet? Was it sleet or snow?
What's going on with the seasons?
I'm just singing on my own.
In areas where it snows a lot,
That's nice. I haven't made a snowman.
I wanna have a snowball fight.
I wanna have a serious snowball fight.
I wanna do it for real.
If you get hit a few times, you're out.
But how would I do that on stream?
"Put rocks in it." That's against the rules!
I feel like you should see it.
Better if you can see it.
I was thinking about what to do for next year's Setsubun.
I've been doing Ehomaki (Sushi Roll) taste comparisons.
Next year I want to do something different.
Usually for things I wanna do, preparations...
Need to start thinking about it a year in advance or I won't make it.
I was thinking vaguely about it. Vaguely.
I, the Oni, will be on standby in the studio...
And do a call-in waiting for people to come throw beans.
Throwing beans at the Oni is fine.
Throwing beans at me because you want to hit me is fine.
Or for venting frustration unrelated to me.
I was thinking about it a little.
It's an event for me, you know.
Something only an Oni can do.
Since I can, I wanna do something fun.
But yeah, I vaguely thought it sounded funny.
Oh right, I want to release Setsubun merch too.
So maybe I'll reveal the merch based on how many people come to throw beans.
I'll set the number properly later.
Even people who just really want to hit me with beans are fine.
There's only one Oni in Hololive, after all.
Won't you collab with me on beans?
But maybe sweet bean snacks I can eat.
That's about all I came up with.
I end up thinking about stuff.
After eating the Ehomaki the other day...
I feel like I could eat their bean snacks.
I kinda want to see it.
Eh, is it okay? Is it?
"It's pitiful to hit Yo with beans."
specifically to get hit next year.
But if it's online, it's easy to come.
Coming to the studio is a pretty high hurdle.
Or someone totally free that day with time to kill.
"Funny if someone throws while passing by."
But if they happen to be there...
Members who came to the studio for other things?
Holomem who come just to throw beans.
I really want them to come.
Or I'll have them eat it.
I don't know if the Ehomaki collab will happen next year.
True, just coming to throw beans is...
I don't know if they'll let me do it again.
Since we're doing it, we should eat together.
Next year, let's do a Bean Throwing Call-in.
Managers who are okay with appearing.
There's another manager I'm close with.
I like them quite a bit.
So I gave them to the two of them.
Every time I see them, they show me.
And showed me a video of them washing it.
There were a few different expressions.
I gave them the ones that look like their expressions.
"It looks like you, Mane-chan! This face looks like you, so here."
I like Chiikawa, and Hachiware, and Momonga too.
I like a lot of them.
Yeah, I like most of them.
What was it... there was something I wanted to talk about.
What was I gonna talk about?
Should I check my phone? Oh, I already talked about the Apple Watch.
Dinner with Shishi (Botan)? Not yet, next month maybe?
We're busy. Our schedules didn't match up exactly.
Invited me to a collab recently.
Yeah, I was on the Kamigokke Radio.
At that time, we said, "Let's go eat."
"We haven't gone yet, have we?" We talked about that.
Shishi was acting kinda weird though.
We talked about it during the Mukai-yon collab too.
When I said "Shiina-san seems acts weird,"
They said, "She's not usually like that."
"I think she really likes you, Ayame-chan."
Maybe I seemed that interesting and mysterious?
But what does that mean, "charm is amazing"?
It's too abstract, I don't get it.
I don't really have that kind of appeal, though.
I get told that a lot.
Even when I go out with Holomems...
I struggle with that question so much.
I get stuck on that question.
I don't know what to say.
I wondered why I don't know.
I do lots of little things.
So I can't say "I'm doing *this*" consistently.
I do a bit of dance...
So it's really hard. "What am I doing?"
I don't even know myself. Sometimes I start cleaning or decluttering suddenly.
Sometimes I go to voice training.
That's it. "I'm doing a bunch of stuff."
It's hard to explain. When asked, you don't list, "I did this, and that, and that."
That question stumps me. I just say, "I'm doing various things."
Or when it's too hard to explain, I just say, "What *am* I doing? I don't know."
If asked deeply, I say that. "I don't really know what I'm doing."
It doesn't expand the conversation. I get stuck.
Troubling. "Still mysterious." Is that mysterious? If you knew the inside, you'd be like, "Wow, shallow."
Sometimes I'm not thinking, sometimes I am.
True, maybe it's hard to tell from the outside.
No way you guys can know.
I get lost easily, so I decide that.
But other actions, I don't decide at all.
Like, decide the night before what to do tomorrow.
but deciding "I want to do this, this, and this."
Like walking, I want to decide properly.
But since I bought an Apple Watch...
I learned after wearing the Apple Watch.
Sitting all the time is bad...
So a ring for how many times you stood up.
If you exercise for a day...
The line grows rounder and rounder.
Eventually it becomes a full circle.
"Let's make 3 circles today as a goal."
Calories maybe? I forgot. But there are 3 types.
When you complete it, it says "You did it!" or "Well done!"
It asks, "Are you walking right now?"
"Standing for more than 1 min per hour..."
Seems to boost my motivation more.
I seem to like seeing measurement data.
Being praised makes me happy, but...
There's a short comment every day.
When I wake up, "What's my score today?"
I set a goal for how many hours to sleep.
Like "Sleep by this time, wake up at this time."
How much I stuck to it affects the number.
So I sleep with the Apple Watch on.
And check it *beep* when I wake up.
I rarely have it off for long.
Basically wearing it all the time.
Better than when it was really bad.
At my worst, I was waking up every 3 hours.
Compared to that, I'm sleeping a lot.
But I sleep around 2 AM now.
I rarely sleep after seeing the sunrise anymore.
I've never had that pop up.
Even when I use Pokémon Sleep...
There's no fun in the morning.
But listening to the recording while you slept...
That's one of the exciting events.
People said, "Maybe the mic isn't working?"
Because when I had a cold...
It sounded like I was dying.
I guess I don't really snore.
That recording part just lacks excitement.
Not getting any audio is boring.
It'd be nice if I talked.
When I went back to my parents' house...
My old room is gone, so...
I was touching Mother Nakiri's arm...
She told me it was super scary.
I have zero memory of it.
Apparently I was laughing while rubbing her arm.
Did I think she was a cat?
But when I was vaguely sleepy...
I heard a voice like "Whoa, startled me!"
Mother Nakiri must have been surprised.
That voice felt like a dream.
But I don't remember touching her or laughing.
That happened, if we're talking about sounds.
I do laugh sometimes while sleeping.
Sometimes I wake myself up with it.
Sometimes I wake up from my own laughter.
I'm not looking at anything though.
And woke up from the panic of hiding it.
I have scary ones like that sometimes.
You don't remember fun dreams, right?
I have precognitive dreams a lot.
"I saw this scene in a dream."
Are my memories getting mixed up?
The gap between the dream and reality is wide.
Usually I see something far ahead.
"I saw this question in a dream!" You don't have that?
If I remembered it clearly and vividly...
If I remembered, I could write it.
But it's totally mundane daily stuff.
Right. "Saw this on Test Zero!" That would be nice.
If I had to name one thing...
It's a story about forensic pathologists.
It's interesting, so I wanted to rewatch it.
Yeah, the drama with Yonezu-san's "Lemon" as the theme song.
"Dubbed? Subbed? Movie?" No, not a movie.
But I didn't know *why* it was interesting.
It was quite a while ago.
They are in the same universe.
Members of "Unnatural" appear in it too.
You don't hear about them much.
And they rarely become dramas, so that's part of it.
but a new case happens each time.
Concluded in one episode, kind of.
But it depicts the absurdity of the world.
The absurdity of the world you can't do anything about.
Because it depicts that, it feels interesting.
There was an episode like that.
There was a boy who was friends with him.
In the end, he couldn't save him.
He wanted to let everyone know.
They didn't kill him with their own hands.
So they couldn't be judged legally.
"Is it okay for me to live?"
There was a really good scene.
His wife... was killed in a murder case. And he dissected her body himself. His wife, I think.
There's a male character with that background.
And that person said to the boy...
"Live so that you can be forgiven." That line really hit me.
You know how in dramas... "The dead Mr. X..."
"He would be happy if you lived." They often tidy it up with pretty words. In stories.
Usually I'd think, "That's nice, but just pretty words."
I couldn't fully buy into it.
But seeing that scene in Unnatural...
Instead of settling it with pretty words...
Whether they forgive you or not, they're dead.
Not tidying it up with pretty words was good.
The way the work was crafted...
"You live so that you can be forgiven."
He said that to the boy.
It really hit me, that scene.
I liked how realistic it was.
A real feeling, not tidied up.
Having dissected his murdered wife... the weight of his words is insane.
So he could say those lines.
It's different from someone with a different background saying it.
He must have thoughts like that.
He doesn't know what she thinks.
Wants to be forgiven by his wife.
Because he thinks that, the words came out.
I just gave a passionate speech.
I love works by the person who wrote "Unnatural".
"Reading the novelization of Unnatural would be fun."
Yeah, I wanna read the book.
Ah, it's an original drama script.
But I think the writer of Unnatural...
Was the same person as "Nigeru wa Haji".
When I checked, I thought, "Eh, the person who wrote Nigehaji?"
Eh, right? It's the same person.
If you're interested, please watch it.
That's basically what I've been watching recently.
It plays during such good scenes.
I have a desire to watch interesting works like that recently.
I want to watch various things.
If you have recommendations, let me know.
The kind that makes you think. Interesting ones.
As for anime... Ah, I watched Ep 1 of Frieren.
Ah, the newly started one too.
I only watched Ep 1 of that, haven't watched more.
I wanted to chill before bed...
I watched Frieren Ep 1, but thought, "Wow, if I watch more, I won't be able to sleep."
I only watched Ep 1 of Frieren.
I feel a similar vibe from that.
I get it, I get it.
"You haven't watched The Super Mario Bros. Movie?"
I plan to, but haven't yet.
Ah right, the Suda Masaki one.
I'm curious but haven't watched it.
I bawled my eyes out at that.
Too good, my tear ducts were destroyed.
What was it... I wanted to talk about something.
I'm looking back at my calendar.
I think I'll announce Valentine's on the 11th.
There will be a stream on Valentine's.
"I can get my hopes up, right?"
Eh, I didn't say I'd give chocolates.
but didn't say I'd give chocolates.
Well, the possibility of you becoming chocolate...
I said there's a Valentine's stream...
"If I become chocolate, will you eat me?"
If it comes to that, I'll eat you deliciously.
Ah, the other day, I got chocolate from my manager.
She gave me a tin of chocolates.
I only ate one so far.
When I went to get the Ehomaki...
"It's a bit early, but happy Valentine's."
Last year, I gave out a lot.
What was it called? You guys remember?
I think I bought that for them.
According to rumors on the wind.
According to rumors, the Valentine Voice is out.
Ah crap, the slide isn't up.
Glad we could do a reissue.
Glad I worked to make it happen.
Everyone was waiting for the hoodie.
There are probably people like that.
But clothes are hard to throw away, aren't they? Or hard to replace?
Like, unless there's clearly a hole...
Even then, you hesitate with clothes.
Don't you? The timing to buy clothes is difficult.
I might have said this before.
The reissue is out, so if it's your favorite...
Eh, I seriously can't throw away T-shirts.
Even if the neck is a bit stretched...
Maybe then I'd throw it out.
If it's just the neck being stretched...
"Wasteful to turn it into a rag."
And so T-shirts just pile up.
I want to buy weird T-shirts too.
Was there anything else I didn't talk about?
Ah, in January I went to dinner with everyone from Melomeru.
It was quite a while ago though.
"Maybe they'll be happy." As a token of thanks.
Letting me call into their streams...
Stuff like that, so for Melomeru members...
I worried about it a lot.
Giving that stuff to girls is hard.
If they didn't like it, it'd be trouble.
Bath salts are just for the bath.
And the design was cute and stylish.
Even if they don't like the smell, it looks cute sitting there.
When we went to Noe-Lami Onikan?
Whenever I meet Lamy-chan at the studio...
Not just studio, whenever we meet.
"Ayame-san, Ayame-senpai, you smell like a really good woman."
What is that? Are our scent preferences similar?
We went to dinner as four.
So we had a moment alone.
But if my memory is correct...
I think I wear different scents each time.
It shouldn't be the same smell every time.
Maybe our preferences are just aligned.
Everyone is nice, so they just say that.
"She said she hesitated to ask what you use."
Even the same perfume smells different on different people.
True, it's hard to ask about perfume.
But if I say it myself, isn't that weird?
"What do you use?" I have so many, seriously.
Seriously, I have enough to be an otaku about it.
I have a lot. Really a lot.
I might be a bit of a perfume otaku.
Eh, what else did I talk about?
Lots of slow life games announced.
Twitter was like "Slow life traffic jam".
"Can't live a slow life at this rate."
I saw a tweet like that.
Watched the Direct the other day.
There was something I was interested in.
Seems I cut it on something.
Animal Crossing got an update too.
Did I cut it with the box cutter?
I have a Chiikawa band-aid on it now.
I said I bought them before.
Never used them, but now I am.
I slammed it into a corner.
Eh, I have no more stories.
Maybe I'll remember something while reading.
When I do a chatting stream...
I talk for like 2 or 3 hours.
Feels like I haven't talked enough.
I feel like there was something.
What was it? This feels gross.
If I remember, I'll say it.
During the time I wasn't streaming...
Taxi drivers kept giving me candy.
That happened! I tweeted it on Sub-account.
There was a period where I got so much candy. It was a mystery.
At first, a driver gave me Pine Candy.
Just thrust a bag of Pine Candy...
"Eh? Are you sure?" And I took it.
I was like, "Eh? Are you sure? Thank you," and took it.
So, a grumpy "Hn!" driver, then a polite driver.
And the third person, the next day...
"Then I'll give you another one!" And gave me more.
3 days in a row, or 3 times in a row...
I forgot if it was consecutive days.
But 3 times in a row taking a taxi...
Seriously a mystery. What was that?
But old men drivers talk to me a lot.
Middle-aged drivers talk to me a lot.
Maybe because I was a grandpa/grandma's kid?
Mystery series... the other day I went to Ichiran alone.
"Ah, fill this out," looked at it.
They handed me a Chinese form.
Funny thing is, Kanji is shared.
I flipped it over and it was Japanese.
I just bowed without saying a word.
Maybe they thought I wasn't Japanese.
"I understand the meaning though," I thought.
Yeah, eating out alone doesn't bother me.
Ichiran is meant for solo dining.
Even with friends, you get separated anyway.
I'm fine either way. Alone or with others.
"How far can you go alone?" I've done Hot Pot. Yakiniku too.
Sushi too. I went to sushi alone and made friends with the foreigner next to me.
What was it... they sent me miso soup... lots happened.
Wait, I didn't initiate the conversation. I can't talk to people!
It's scary! I said this before on stream.
Well, I guess I have charm?
If someone talks to me, I try to be nice.
Well, I guess I'm not without charm?
I wanted to talk about that.
Neko-dorei-san with the letter, thank you.
Are you sure? I'll read silently.
That's right, 1 month until the Fes.
In the blink of an eye.
Ah right, that's how it is.
I'll do my best without pushing too hard.
I know that feeling painfully well.
There's a story I wanted you to hear.
I wanted you to hear it.
If there's a line or it's crowded...
3 tries per person, then rotate to the back of the line.
That's typical recently. If a popular series is crowded, there are restrictions like that.
Places that don't have it, don't.
But listen. It's not necessarily "bad," but it annoyed me.
I went to do Gacha... won't say which one, but I did it.
One I really liked. I found it.
I didn't know exactly how many were left inside.
But since it's popular, I knew there were few left.
I wondered if others wanted to play, so I did 3 pulls first.
I thought I should step aside and rotate.
The person after me was pulling.
I thought, "I'll line up again and pull after her."
The woman who went *after* the person behind me...
She rotated after 3 pulls like normal.
But the next one spent all her money and took them all!
"Ehh! Then I should have just pulled them all!"
The lady in between us... and Yo too...
We were doing the 3-pull rotation nicely.
"If so, I should have just taken them all!"
But taking them all is bad manners, I thought.
This feeling with nowhere to go...
"Don't get the one you want! Get duplicates and suffer!"
"Get nothing but dupes!" This helpless feeling...
I wanted you to hear it.
Do people get cut in line?
Since I got cut in line...
I cursed her. "Get duplicates! Pull the same one!"
But maybe that place had a 3-pull limit too.
If that lady hadn't cut me, I wouldn't have gotten the one I wanted.
Yeah, I actually got it then.
She adjusted the RNG for me.
Lucky. Getting cut helped in the end.
There are still some I don't have.
"How?" I thought. She pulled them all.
The lady in front of me.
I got to pull 3 times, so it's fine.
The rules... where she pulled them all...
There was no "3 per person" rule written there.
I could have just pulled until I got it.
True. I have to tell everyone on stream like this.
To let this feeling pass on (Joobutsu).
Good, I told everyone. It's passed on.
Tada no Genga Azuki-san, thank you.
I said that, they wrote it.
I transferred it to a mini bottle.
A and B, which one is worse?
I caught it 5 years ago and almost died.
Really scary, I hate the flu.
"How happy I was to be healthy."
Not catching a cold is best.
"As a reward, can I get a super Big Smile?"
Aren't the Nakiri-gumi good at Japanese?
Theory: Nakiri-gumi are good at Japanese.
I wanna learn to speak something too.
What kind of questions are there?
Is that okay? Questions like that?
Kononori Norinori na Kirigumi-san, thank you.
"My beloved Ojou, Yahoo! Cheering for you."
"I brought her. Europe doesn't really have..."
"Plushie photo culture, so I got stared at in various places."
"The other day, taking a photo at a mountain peak, the wind was strong..."
"Dangerous, dangerous. Thought my heart would explode."
"Hope Ojou can travel to various places..."
"Even if we are far apart, I'll always love you."
I want to go to Europe.
With Europe, you can visit various places... take a long time and visit Venice, etc.
But I wanna see the European townscapes.
But for people living in Europe, that scenery is just normal from birth.
Do European people think "This townscape is wonderful"?
Maybe you don't feel the charm instantly?
For us who don't have it...
But if it's normal growing up...
Is it like "The grass is always greener"?
Japan doesn't have those townscapes everywhere.
Probably, European circle is small among Yo's...
"In France, they maintain the townscape by law."
That is something to be protected.
"What book are you reading?" I was asked.
Thanks. Happy you read and gave feedback.
"Twin-tails super cute. I had a cold but..."
"Thanks to Ojou's stream, I think I'm cured. Thanks."
"Who can take me with consecutive tickets."
Thanks. Hope you can see it.
Would be nice if you could go.
"As a reward, super-super-super extra large Big Smile..."
"PS: Got lots of prize money, so I'm pushing it to you."
Haven't done Big Smile in this outfit much.
Is it okay to take it?
That's a hell of a name.
Thank you. From here on too...
"Thanks for the chat stream. Cold, so here's tea money."
Tea. Warm tea. Hits the spot recently.
"Enjoyed the leisurely chat after a while."
"I watched Super Mario Bros recently too."
"By the way, I went to all stages/expo at 4th Fes."
"Looking forward to seeing Ojou sing and dance on stage again this year."
"Delicious and fun things Yo-chan mentioned on stream..."
For the Fes people are coming to...
Gotta make it hype no matter what.
Chou Kaguya-hime Issho ni Miyou-san, thank you.
Oh, lots of people doing it.
What does it say in Korean?
I'm starting to feel a bit bad for you.
I don't have Poyoyo with me.
Please wait a moment, I'll change costumes.
Do this like this, and this like that...
How's that? Did you see it?
This is synced with Yo's mouth right now.
Ah, is this the first time showing it synced?
The outfit changed, so it's kinda...
Been a while since I brought this outfit out.
It's bugging out a bit and I can't put the hair ornament on, though.
I kinda lost the hair ornament. Dropped it or something.
Might have left it on the bus.
It'd be hilarious if nobody gets this reference.
Um, "Ojou, thanks for the fun chat..."
Do your best, do your best!
Saying "do your best" feels a bit irresponsible, and I wonder if it's okay, but...
Seems they want me to say "do your best" and give them a push.
Seems they've been entrusted with a new project-like thing and are nervous.
...this outfit was included too, so like, really...
My hair sways super, super much.
You didn't sway this much before, you!
Hey Raba-san, thank you. Good luck.
You'll be fine. You can do it.
Ah, it says "silent reading is fine".
Then I'll read it a bit.
The storage service I told you about the other day...
It makes me happy you're using it.
Gaspa-chan, thanks for the SC too.
